snippet.textDisplay:
If you use multiple Apple products like iPhone, iPad, Macbook, do yourself a favor and get the real ones. I got fake ones and if I wanted to switch Airpods connection from iPhone to Macbook, you have to turn off or disconnect from iPhone first, and then connect fake Airpods to Macbook; that got annoying very quickly. So I bought REAL ones and the transition between Apple products is so easy. I can also be using the RIGHT Airpod then seamlessly switch to LEFT Airpod, something fake Airpods or any wireless earbuds can't do without having to connect LEFT earbud separately.


I've used so many in-ear wireless buds so I'm very used to the ear pressure feeling. I've been so spoiled by the real Airpods Pro, on how comfortable they are because of their pressure valve design, I can't go back to using regular in-ear buds. These fake ones have stickers for pressure valves, how silly.

I've been so spoiled by the real Airpods Pro, on how comfortable they are because of their pressure valve design, I can't go back to using regular in-ear buds. These fake ones have stickers for pressure valves, how silly.
